 the neck. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  It's not really a bad thing - since this isn't VN, all opinions will at least get a glance over.<br>
<br>
Anyways, Temmie, I feel you're acceptance of your performance is due to your perspective of play. You see yourself perform to a reasonable level on your own terms. But once compared to how well others perform in situations that YOU are suppose to surpass everyone else in (chasing/killing casters and support, hurting but not reliably killing tanks), you'll notice that you'll fall a pretty large margin behind. When you RvR, try to imagine a another melee class in your place. If you know about a polearmsman or a reaver and how well they perform, I think you'll start to see us being left behind as a damage class, and you'll start to feel like we're not dragging our own weight.<br>
<br>
The difference between an anytime and no style is about 50 points worth of damage (with the slash line spec). However, thrust giving no real anytime, the difference can be subsequented with more oppertunitys to use your reactionary and positionals. Pretty sure you won't be missing out on your anytimes damage.<br>
<br>
The styles review should yeild some interesting information about us. We may not even need anything else besides improving our styles (I remember our growth rates are only slightly better than the growth rates of the styles in the slash line, and behind advanced spec lines like pole, two hand, flexible, ect. If we got better growth rate on all our styles, that could very well make us set offensivly). <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
