<br>
That leaves arms and the only way they get more dmg out is with a much slower 2h weapon (pole or 2h). Even then while their dmg per hit may be higher it rapidly evens out (in my experiance ofc). Slower weapons make it harder to proc PF and they're much more suseptable to missing, bt, guard and all that. I rarely, if ever, see my attacks blocked by a guard due to the penalty assosiated with blocking dual-wielders. Also missing one of my attacks means very little to me most of the time, I'll swing again soon especially since I take haste charges with me since I rarely run with a theurg. Arms do, however, have better hp and defense and make a great assist partner for a merc. <p>~Temos Shadowsoul~<br>
