I repeat what the grab bag said:<br>
<br>
Q: A lot of people say Midgard twohanded does ~+15% damage bonus vs. onehanded, and in Hibernia and Albion (as they have special speccs) twohanded does ~+40% damage bonus vs onehanded. I'm talking about style damage. Is that quite correct?<br>
<br>
A: Just as a side note, be very afraid of things that &quot;a lot of people&quot; say. For some reason unknown to mortal man, &quot;a lot of people&quot; tend to be either wrong, or not very many people after all. <br>
<br>
But that's not the answer to your question! The answer according to the swell guy who looked it up is &quot;All two handed weapons get a base 10% damage bonus, plus an extra amount based on their specialization level.&quot;<br>
<br>
&lt;mutters about her lack of willpower in discussing this tired old subject&gt;<br>
