<br>
Well, there are stealthers..<br>
<br>
&quot;Can anyone tell me what roll im supposed to play in an RvR group?&quot;<br>
<br>
You're an extra pair of hands. Meaning, you arn't the primary damage dealer or Primary tank. You are a damage add for the polearmsman, or equally slow swinging tank that can't get past bladeturn. In most cases, you only compliment anothers skills. Some cases, you are actually needed, like the polearmsman who cannot take the time to switch between a pole and a quicker one hander. Not what you invisioned, I bet, but that's what mythic is telling us and the only way we are of any use.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why should groups WANT me?&quot;<br>
<br>
For the same reason they will want an armsman, paladin or reaver. You have the possibility to attract an enemys attention while the casters do the damage. You also have the oppertunity to interupt other casters that arn't high RR (aka, don't have MoC). You're also the clean up boy once most of the fighting is done and the rest are retreating, since casters go through mana real quickly, they don't want to waste time with the last few survivers.<br>
<br>
&quot;A wise man once said something about adapting or deleting....<br>
I ask you... adapt to what?&quot;<br>
<br>
To being a breathing damage add, is the only awnser I can really come up with. In the whole lump some scene in RvR, we are not special. We are expendable.<br>
<br>
We do have our place in PvE though. Amazing what you can do when you have control over a situation. <p>&quot;We will never be what Mythic promised we would when DAoC started, we might as well adapt or delete.&quot; -Avandor<br>
