Mercs are not that much different than armsmen except they do slightly less damage in fights but they offer other benefits (dirty tricks being the main one and charge and suffer less from BT).  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vasagh>Vasagh</A> at: 7/31/03 9:22 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dork of the Month~!</span><br>  Posts: 593<br> <font color=#000000>(7/31/03 9:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=278.topic&index=61>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Merc damage</span><hr size=1> Eh, Vas is correct here, the Grab Bag report of Base 10% damage is for classes that can spec 2H weapons (i.e. Shammy or Healer can USE 2H weapons, but don't get the base damage boost).  The 40-50% damage bonus for 50+ spec is also about right, the boost goes up with more Spec. <p>Nirala Kindred<br>
